    <thetext>Steps:
1. Enable usestatuswhiteboard in Bugzilla
2. Enter a text with line breaks in the task editor in the Status Whiteboard field and submit 
3. Update the bug through the web interface

The line breaks are lost since the status white board is only a single line field in the web ui (e.g. http://mylyn.org/bugzilla-4.0.10/show_bug.cgi?id=1).</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
    <commentid>2255588</commentid>
    <comment_count>1</comment_count>
    <who name="Steffen Pingel">steffen.pingel</who>
    <bug_when>2013-05-12 13:16:41 -0400</bug_when>
    <thetext>Frank, do you have any ideas? Since the whiteboard would be more useful if it allowed line breaks we could consider submitting a request to Bugzilla. Otherwise we would have to consider changing Mylyn to treat the whiteboard as a single line field.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
    <commentid>2256242</commentid>
    <comment_count>2</comment_count>
    <who name="Frank Becker">eclipse</who>
    <bug_when>2013-05-13 13:20:56 -0400</bug_when>
    <thetext>Here the definition from Bugzilla:
Whiteboard
Each bug has a free-form single line text entry box for adding tags and status information.

So it was my fault to create it from kind TaskAttribute.TYPE_LONG_RICH_TEXT instead of TaskAttribute.TYPE_SHORT_TEXT.

If you need a  whiteboard field with line breaks  please use a custom field.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
